728224f-b.text:
Woodhaven Boulevard, east side, north from Fleet Street (White Pot Road) showing at the corner the site upon which stood the White Pot schoolhouse from 1852 to 1896.  In the background is seen Thos. Tompkins farmhouse in 65th Road.  The school house was erected on land donated by Jacobus Springstein son of Casper Springstein.  The first school was established in 1739.  The demolished structure was the fourth or fifth erected on this site.

April 1923.
Views 2&3: March 1925.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection

728222f-a.text:
Woodhaven Boulevard (Trotting Course Lane), at the N.E. corner of Fleet Street (White Pot Road), showing the Whitepot School House.  It appears in the J. L. Riker map of 1852 and still appears as a school house in 1891.  In 1909, G. Lappe owned this corner and the buildings thereon.  The school house does not appear in the Queens Atlas of 1929.

Arthur White.
